<paragraph id="016C1165FF96394EE9F3C25BFC425EB7" blockId="56.[706,957,1383,1410]" box="[706,957,1383,1410]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF96394EE9F3C25BFCF25EB4" authority="Radcliffe, 1913" authorityName="Radcliffe" authorityYear="1913" box="[706,781,1384,1410]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Neobythitinae">Genus</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EE825C254FC425EB7" bold="true" box="[788,957,1383,1409]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">incertae sedis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF96394EEBD2C29AFA815D96" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF96394EEBD2C29AFEAA5EF5" blockId="56.[227,341,1449,1475]" box="[227,341,1449,1475]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<heading id="5A24A609FF96394EEBD2C29AFEAA5EF5" bold="true" box="[227,341,1449,1475]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EEBD2C29AFEAA5EF5" bold="true" box="[227,341,1449,1475]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF96394EEBD2C2E4FA815D96" blockId="56.[227,1439,1495,1697]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
“ 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF96394EEBC1C2E4FE855EC7" authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1885" box="[240,378,1495,1521]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Neobythites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EEBC1C2E4FE855EC7" box="[240,378,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Neobythites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EEAA0C2E4FE075EC7" box="[401,504,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">rotundus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF96394EE93BC2E4FD585EC7" author="Muller" box="[522,679,1495,1521]" firstAuthor="Muller" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref55491" refString="Muller A. 1999. Ichthyofaunen aus dem atlantischen Tertiar der USA. Leipziger Geowissenschaften 9 / 10: 1 - 360." type="journal article" year="1999">Müller, 1999</bibRefCitation>
) and “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EE9CBC2EBFCF15EC7" box="[762,782,1496,1521]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">N</emphasis>
.” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EE81DC2EBFC5F5EC7" box="[812,928,1496,1521]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">virginicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FF96394EE89BC2E4FBB85EC7" author="Muller" box="[938,1095,1495,1521]" firstAuthor="Muller" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 360" refId="ref55491" refString="Muller A. 1999. Ichthyofaunen aus dem atlantischen Tertiar der USA. Leipziger Geowissenschaften 9 / 10: 1 - 360." type="journal article" year="1999">Müller, 1999</bibRefCitation>
, two species that are known from the Atlantic Coastal Plain only (Piney Point Formation), are incertae sedis 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF96394EEFA8C2C9FAC05D22" authorityName="Radcliffe" authorityYear="1913" box="[1177,1343,1530,1556]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Neobythitinae">Neobythitinae</taxonomicName>
that are not clairly related to other living or fossil genera of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF96394EE872C12EFC125D01" authorityName="Radcliffe" authorityYear="1913" box="[835,1005,1565,1591]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Neobythitinae">Neobythitinae</taxonomicName>
. Otoliths of “ 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FF96394EEFB8C12EFAEC5D01" authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1885" box="[1161,1299,1565,1591]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Neobythites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EEFB8C12EFAEC5D01" box="[1161,1299,1565,1591]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Neobythites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EEE19C12DFA635D01" box="[1320,1436,1566,1591]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">virginicus</emphasis>
have a deep ventral area and a small but well-marked antero-dorsal angle. Those of “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EEE33C172FAE25D6C" box="[1282,1309,1601,1626]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">N.</emphasis>
” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF96394EEE04C173FA635D6C" box="[1333,1436,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">rotundus</emphasis>
are easily recognizable by their height which is more considerable than their length, their important thickness, which is essentially located in their posterior portion, and by a salient antero-dorsal angle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
